A 19-year-old man has bee shot and killed in Port Elizabeth s northern areas, Eastern Cape police said on Tuesday. Police spokesperson Colonel Priscilla Naidu said Tony Ferreira was walking with a friend to a shop in Kleinskool on Monday night when they were approached by three unknown men. Naidu said the men allegedly started shooting at the pair. Ferreira was taken to hospital, but later died. Police are investigating a case of murder and attempted murder. Meanwhile, in a separate incident a 26-year old man was shot in the leg while walking home in Helenvale. The victim was confronted by three males who questioned him about a cellphone. One of the suspects pulled out a firearm and shot him, said Naidu. Police are investigating a case of attempted murder.